<subSubSection pageId="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,260,285]" pageId="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species of 
<taxonomicName box="[532,599,261,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Naxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[532,599,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="1">Naxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to the Southern Hemisphere between 
<number box="[1189,1220,260,284]" pageId="1" value="24.0">24</number>
°S and 
<number box="[1301,1334,260,284]" pageId="1" value="42.0">42</number>
°S. Three of the five species only occur in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[621,727,295,320]" name="Australia" pageId="1">Australia</collectingCountry>
, one in southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[963,1066,295,320]" name="Australia" pageId="1">Australia</collectingCountry>
and at Kermadec Island north of 
<collectingCountry box="[151,305,332,357]" name="New Zealand" pageId="1">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Poore" box="[324,461,332,356]" pageId="1" refString="Poore, G. C. B. (2004) Marine decapod Crustacea of Southern Australia: a guide to identification. CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne. 574 pp." type="book" year="2004">
Poore 
<number box="[403,461,332,356]" pageId="1" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and the fifth in 
<collectingCountry box="[670,742,332,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="1">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The 
<collectingCountry box="[812,914,332,357]" name="Australia" pageId="1">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[977,1132,332,357]" name="New Zealand" pageId="1">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
records are from the low intertidal to about 
<quantity box="[356,428,368,392]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.08" pageId="1" unit="m" value="108.0">108 m</quantity>
, where the sea-surface temperature can get as low as 
<number box="[1023,1075,367,392]" pageId="1" value="11.5">11.5</number>
°C. 
<taxonomicName box="[1114,1288,367,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Naxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1114,1288,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="1">Naxia atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1293,1356,367,392]" pageId="1" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1293,1356,367,392]" pageId="1">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
occurs in southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[326,394,404,429]" name="Brazil" pageId="1">Brazil</collectingCountry>
at depths greater than in 
<collectingCountry box="[676,779,404,429]" name="Australia" pageId="1">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[832,985,404,429]" name="New Zealand" pageId="1">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, with bottom temperatures ranging from 
<number box="[151,165,439,464]" pageId="1" value="6.0">6</number>
°C to 
<number box="[230,258,440,464]" pageId="1" value="18.0">18</number>
°C (
<bibRefCitation author="Esteves" box="[303,519,439,464]" pageId="1" refString="Esteves, P. C., Jacques, G. &amp; Panouse, M. (1988) Grands traits de l'hydrologie au large des cotes du Bresil. In: Guille, A. &amp; Ramos, J. M. (Eds.), Les rapports des campagnes a la mer TAAF MD 55 / Bresil, 6 mai - 2 juin 1987. Technical Report 87 - 03. La Riche, Instaprint, 198 pp." type="book" year="1988">
Esteves 
<emphasis box="[397,446,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="1">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[460,519,440,464]" pageId="1" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Stramma" box="[531,698,440,464]" pageId="1" refString="Stramma, L. (1999) On the water masses and mean circulation of the South Atlantic Ocean. Journal of Geophysical Research, 104 (C 9), 20863 - 20883. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1029 / 1999 JC 900139" type="journal article" year="1999">
Stramma 
<number box="[638,698,440,464]" pageId="1" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
